<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./css/general.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./css/content.css">
    <title>Stocks but Stupid - News</title>
</head>
<body>
    {{>navbar}}
    <img id="thumbnail" src="./img/news.jpg" alt="News thumbnail">
    <div id="thumbnail-cover"></div>
    <div id="thumbnail-push"></div>
    <div id="message">
        <p style="font-size: 36px;">Let the virtual news guide you to what stocks to buy next!</p>
    </div>
    <div class="divider"></div>
    <div style="height: 20vh;" class="left-right">
        <div style="flex: 2;">
            <h2>Welcome!</h2>
            <p>Hello, and welcome to <span style="color: rgb(0, 158, 0);">Stocks but Stupid</span>!
            This website was created fully using Node.JS on the server-side and Handlebars on the
            client-side. This project was started on 12/12/2020, and was made to relieve some boredom
            during the coronavirus pandemic.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="flex: 1; border-left: 2px solid black;">
            <img height="200" src="./img/logo.png" alt="SBS Logo">
        </div>
    </div>
    <div style="height: 20vh; border-bottom: none;" class="left-right">
        <div style="flex: 1; border-right: 2px solid black;">
            <img style="border-radius: 100px;" height="200" src="./img/cupofmoney.jpg" alt="Cup of Money">
        </div>
        <div style="flex: 2;">
            <h2>How Do I Start?</h2>
            <p>To start playing, click on the <a style="letter-spacing: 0.07em; color: blue;" href="/register">Register</a> 
            button and create an account. This website works like the normal stock market, except
            completely simulated and fictional, even premade with custom events! This is because I 
            don't have the money to afford the raw JSON data to real stock market prices.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>